---
description: Token-efficient interaction policy with high signal and low verbosity
alwaysApply: true
---

# Default Interaction Mode

- Default to concise, high-signal responses.
- Expand only when user asks for deeper detail.
- Avoid repeating confirmed context from previous turns.

# Tool Usage Efficiency

- Prefer targeted reads/searches over broad scans.
- Batch independent tool calls in parallel.
- Reuse previously gathered facts instead of re-running the same checks.
- Avoid unnecessary browser/MCP actions when file/tool evidence is enough.

# Output Compression Rules

- Use short bullet lists for decisions and outcomes.
- Summarize logs; include raw output only when user requests it.
- For large tasks, provide:
  - what changed
  - why it matters
  - next action
- Keep default response target to 4-8 lines unless task complexity requires more.

# Clarification Discipline

- Ask at most one blocking question at a time.
- If uncertainty is low, proceed with best safe assumption and state it briefly.
